{"word":"ἀπόλαυσις","slug":"ἀπόλαυσις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπόλαυσις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀπολαύω'><el>ἀπολαύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>enjoyment, fruition</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>advantage got from</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <el>ἀπόλαυσιν εἰκοῦς</el> (<a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>) <i>as a reward for</i> your resemblance, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}